---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
import Hero from '../components/sections/Hero.astro'

import heroImage from '../assets/images/hero/about.jpg'
import missionImage from '../assets/images/mission.jpg'
import fandomImage from '../assets/images/fandom.jpg'

import Content from '../components/sections/Content.astro'
import Peep from '../components/Peep.astro'
import Socials from '../content/socials.astro'
import Faq from '../content/Faq.astro'
import FaqItem from '../content/FaqItem.astro'
---

<Base>
  <Hero headline="About Flüüfff – where memories take root" image={heroImage}>
    <p>Flüüfff is a place where creatures gather, friendships grow, and creativity runs wild.</p>
    <p>Here’s everything you need to know about our little corner of the forest.</p>
  </Hero>
  <Content headline="What is Flüüfff?" bg="darker">
    <p>
      Flüüfff 2025 is the 7th edition of the Flüüfff convention.<br />
      It is all about bringing furries together in one place to share friendship, fun, and creativity — values our community
      can be proud of. You don’t have to be a furry to join the celebration!
    </p>

    <p>
      The convention lasts 5 days and can be enjoyed in many ways:<br /> Dance like a party animal, lounge with friends,
      play board-games, attend panels or participate in one of the many activities.
    </p>
  </Content>
  <Content headline="Our mission" sideImage={missionImage} right id="mission">
    <p>
      Flüüfff is Belgium’s premier furry convention—a vibrant, five-day celebration of anthropomorphic creativity,
      community, and joy. Held annually in Brussels, Flüüfff brings together furries and friends from across Europe and
      beyond to share in a spirit of inclusivity, imagination, and fun.
    </p>

    <p>
      We are more than just a convention; we are a gathering of kindred spirits who value friendship, self-expression,
      and the boundless possibilities of the furry fandom. Whether you're dancing like a party animal, lounging with new
      friends, showcasing your fursuit, or participating in panels and games, Flüüfff is your space to be your authentic
      self.
    </p>

    <p>
      Each edition of Flüüfff is themed—from seaside holidays and abbey adventures to tropical islands and grand
      casinos—offering fresh experiences and memories year after year. Our commitment to creativity, respect, and
      community ensures that everyone feels welcome, whether you're a seasoned furry or a curious newcomer.
    </p>

    <p>
      As a registered non-profit organization (ASBL), we reinvest all proceeds into enhancing future events or
      supporting charitable causes, reflecting our dedication to giving back to the community that makes Flüüfff
      possible.
    </p>

    <p>Come as you are, leave as part of the Flüüfff family.</p>
  </Content>
  <Content headline="What is the furry fandom?" sideImage={fandomImage}>
    <p>
      The furry fandom is a community inspired by anthropomorphic animals (animals with human traits).<br />
      People who are part of the fandom are called furries.
    </p>
    <p>You can compare it to other fan communities like Star Wars, anime, or fantasy fairs.</p>
    <p>
      The furry fandom is mainly about creativity and is also known as a very social community. Most furries create
      their own character (also called a fursona), based on a certain animal, real or otherwise.
    </p>
    <p>
      There are regular animals, hybrids, mythical creatures, and some even invent their own species. If there’s a
      meetup or convention, you’ll likely find people wearing fursuits — costumes based on their fursona.
    </p>
    <p>
      At conventions and within the community, it’s all about creating art, writing stories, roleplaying, socializing,
      and making and wearing fursuits.
    </p>
    <p>Most furry conventions and several furry groups also raise funds and organize panels for various charities.</p>
  </Content>
  <Content headline="Meet the Dream Team" bg="primary-light" id="dreamteam">
    <p>
      Flüüfff wouldn’t happen without the amazing crew working behind the scenes.<br />
      From handling the big picture to sorting out the smallest details, our team of staff and volunteers makes sure everything
      runs smoothly.
    </p>
    <p>They’re the ones making sure the con feels like home — year after year.</p>
